{{Infobox film | name = Au nom du Christ | image = Au_Nom_Du_Christ.jpg | caption = | director = [[Roger Gnoan M’Bala]] | producer = Amka Films Productions, S.A. | writer = | starring = Pierre Gondo, Naky Savane, Akissi Delta, Felix Lago, Martin Guedeba | distributor = | released = 1993 | runtime = 85 min | country = Ivory Coast | language = French | budget = | gross = | screenplay = Roger Gnoan M’Bala, Jean-Marie Adiaffi, Bernin Akaffou | cinematography = Mohammed Soudani | sound = Jean-Pierre Fenié | editing = Djangoye Amoussy | music = Paul Wassaba }}
'''''Au nom du Christ''''' is a 1993 Ivorian film directed by Roger Gnoan M’Bala. It won the Grand Prize for Best Film at the [[FESPACO]] Film Festival and Nominated for the [[Golden Leopard]] Award at the [[Locarno International Film Festival]] in 1993.<ref>{{Cite web |title=History of Cinema in Côte d'Ivoire |work= |publisher=Film Birth |year= |url=http://www.filmbirth.com/cote_d_ivoire.html |doi= |accessdate=20 February 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130117052421/http://www.filmbirth.com/cote_d_ivoire.html/ |archivedate=January 17, 2013 }}
</ref>
== Synopsis == In this scathing satirical drama that takes place in a village of West Africa, an untutored pig-keeper who has been thrown out of his home falls into a river and has a vision which sends him back to his people to save them for [[Jesus Christ]], introducing himself as Magloire I, “the cousin of Christ.” A little crazy, a little robber, while some think he is a charlatan and others think he is a prodigy, he reigns as an absolute master and pushes his convictions to extremes, like being crucified. This movie recalls with humour the proliferation of pseudo-Christian sects and the outrageous acts they can convey in a continent like [[Africa]], tossed about tradition, modernity and power.
