Karel de Grote college is a [[Netherlands|Dutch]] [[Waldorf school]] named after [[Charlemagne]] or Charles the Great, King of the Franks. The school is located near the centre of [[Nijmegen]] and has around 750 students, most of whom are from Nijmegen but a large number from outer cities and towns such as Arnhem, Cuijk and Wageningen also find their way to this school.

