'''National Highway 7''' or National Road No.7 (10007) ({{AHN-AH|11|K}}) is one of the national [[highway]]s of [[Cambodia]]. With a length of 509.17&nbsp;km  it connects [[Skuon]] with [[Trapeang Kreal]], international border checkpoint with [[Laos]]. It is part of [[Asian Highway Network]] and of the connection by road between [[Phnom Penh]] and [[Vientiane]], joining [[Route 13 (Laos)|Route 13]] in Laos leading north along the Mekong to [[Luang Prabang]].

In November 2004 it was announced that the reconstruction of the road, assisted by the Chinese government, would be partly rebuilt by China's [[Shanghai Construction Group]].<ref>{{cite web|url=
http://english.peopledaily.com.cn/200411/18/eng20041118_164353.html|title=Cambodia builds national road with Chinese assistance|publisher=English People Daily|date=November 18, 2004|accessdate=January 28, 2009}}</ref> 
The public work, costing totally about US$80 million, was officially inaugurated on 29 April 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cambodiamirror.wordpress.com/2008/05/01/wednesday-3042008-economic-dragon-for-cambodia-samdech-prime-minister-shows-his-stance-to-continue-to-restore-and-build-infrastructure/|title=Economic Dragon for Cambodia|publisher=The Mirror|date=April 30, 2008|accessdate=June 20, 2010}}</ref>

