'''V Corps''' of the [[Korean People's Army]] was created before January, 1951.
Consisted of at least 3 divisions on January 7, 1951, when 2 divisions attacked the [[2nd Infantry Division (United States)|U.S. 2nd Infantry Division]] in a frontal attack, while a third division attacked from the northwest against the adjacent [[8th Infantry Division (South Korea)|ROK 8th Division]]. They were assisted by one of the divisions of the [[II Corps (North Korea)|NKPA II Corps]], which also launched attacks against the neighboring [[III Corps (South Korea)|ROK III Corps]] to the east. The North Koreans managed to force the 2d Division out of [[Wonju]] by the evening of January 7, and all counterattacks failed to retake the city.<ref>{{Cite book| url = http://www.history.army.mil/brochures/kw-chinter/chinter.htm| title = The Korean War: The Chinese Intervention| publisher = [[United States Army Center of Military History]]| first = Richard W. |last = Stewart| id = CMH Pub 19-8}}</ref>
==See also== {{Portal|North Korea|War}} *[[I Corps (North Korea)|I Corps]] *[[II Corps (North Korea)|II Corps]] *[[III Corps (North Korea)|III Corps]] *[[IV Corps (North Korea)|IV Corps]] *[[XII Corps (North Korea)|XII Corps]]
==References== {{reflist}}
[[Category:Military units and formations of North Korea in the Korean War|Corps0005]] [[Category:Corps of North Korea|Corps0005NK]]
