{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2014}} {{Infobox civilian attack |title= Vučitrn massacre |image=Vushtrri 2006.PNG |caption=Location of Vučitrn in Kosovo |location= [[Vučitrn]], [[Kosovo]], [[FR Yugoslavia]] |target= [[Kosovo Albanian]] [[refugees]] |date= 2-3 May 1999 |time= |timezone= [[Central European Time]] |type= Mass Killing |fatalities= 100–120 |injuries= |perps= [[Police of the Republic of Serbia|Serbian Police]] |motive= }} {{Campaignbox Kosovo War}} The '''Vučitrn massacre''' was the mass killing of [[Kosovo Albanian]] [[refugees]] near [[Vučitrn]], during the [[Kosovo War]] on 2-3 May 1999.
==Background== A column of about 1,000 refugees were travelling in a convoy of about 100 [[tractor]]s, who were fleeing fighting between the [[Kosovo Liberation Army|KLA]] and Serbian forces east of Vučitrn.<ref name=Independent>{{cite news|last=Bruce|first=Cabell|title=Serb war criminals seize north Kosovo|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/serb-war-criminals-seize-north-kosovo-1112934.html|newspaper=The Independent|date=August 15, 1999}}</ref> [[Police of the Republic of Serbia|Serbian Police]] and [[List of Serbian paramilitary formations|paramilitary]] forces caught up with the convoy that traveled south. On 2-3 May between Gornja Sudimlja and Donja Sudimlja ({{lang-sq|Studime e Eperme and Studime e Poshtme}}) near Vučitrn, an estimated one hundred men were killed.<ref name=HRW>{{cite book|title=Under Orders: War Crimes in Kosovo|year=2001|publisher=Human Rights Watch|url=http://www.unhcr.org/refworld/pdfid/3c2b204a0.pdf|chapter=Vucitrn (Vushtrri) Municipality|accessdate=25 December 2015}}</ref>
[[ICTY]] investigator Romeu Ventura stated that 120 civilians were murdered on 2 May by Serb forces and buried two days later in a mass grave five miles east of Vučitrn.<ref name=Independent/> After the war, ICTY forensic teams discovered 98 bodies in Gornja Sudimlja.<ref name=HRW/>
The Vučitrn case was raised at the trial of Serbian police general [[Vlastimir Đorđević]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Vlastimir Đorđević Convicted for Crimes in Kosovo|url=http://www.icty.org/sid/10606|newspaper=ICTY|date=23 February 2011}}</ref> The indictment against Đorđević says that some 105 Kosovo Albanians were killed in the massacre near the village of Sudimlje on 2 May 1999.<ref>{{cite news|title=POLICE CRIMES IN VUCITRN|url=http://www.sense-agency.com/icty/police-crimes-in-vucitrn.29.html?cat_id=1&news_id=11185|newspaper=SENSE Tribunal|date=4 January 2009}}</ref> Đorđević was sentenced to 27 years in prison.<ref>{{cite web|title=Case Information Sheet: Vlastimir Đorđević|url=http://www.icty.org/x/cases/djordjevic/cis/en/cis_djordjevic_en.pdf|publisher=ICTY|accessdate=25 December 2015}}</ref>
